  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Employement of Syrian refugees at Dutch companies in Turkey</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Employment of Syrian refugees at Dutch companies in Turkey is a project which goes beyond humanitarian aid and aims to provide a solid future for Syrian refugees living in Turkey. In the year 2017 the project is basically a pilot to establish an infrastructure and approach to help syrian refugees to a job, preferably with Dutch companies in Turkey. The project is made possible with the financial support of the Dutch Ministry of Foreign Affairs. A total of 200 placements is envisaged. Furthermore a database for jobopportunities and skilled laborforce under refugees will be established, as well as trainingcourses and other instruments for jobplacements</narrative>
  </description>
  <participating-org activity-id="PPR-29396" ref="XM-DAC-7" role="1" type="10">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ministry of Foreign Affairs of The Netherlands</narrative>
  </participating-org>
  <activity-status code="1"></activity-status>
  <activity-date iso-date="2016-11-01" type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Althuogh the project started officially on November 1 2016, due to the various preparations which had to be made, the activities on the ground (Turkey) started at the beginning of 2017</narrative>
  </activity-date>
  <activity-date iso-date="2017-12-31" type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The activities will be finalised by the end of this year. If the approach turnes out to be succesfull a continuation is envisaged.</narrative>
  </activity-date>
